theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  classical
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately and conclude by antisymmetry.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction: `interior Aᶜ ⊆ (closure A)ᶜ`
    intro x hx
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` contained in `Aᶜ`.
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hx with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
    -- Show that `x ∉ closure A`; otherwise we derive a contradiction.
    have h_not_closure : x ∉ closure (A : Set X) := by
      intro hx_cl
      -- From `hx_cl` we get that `U ∩ A` is non‐empty.
      have h_nonempty : ((U : Set X) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff.1 hx_cl) U hU_open hxU
      -- But `U ⊆ Aᶜ`, hence the intersection is empty, contradiction.
      rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hyA⟩⟩
      have : y ∈ (Aᶜ : Set X) := hU_subset hyU
      exact this hyA
    -- Reinterpret `¬ x ∈ closure A` as membership in the complement.
    simpa using h_not_closure
  · -- `⊇` direction: `(closure A)ᶜ ⊆ interior Aᶜ`
    intro x hx
    -- The set `(closure A)ᶜ` is open.
    have h_open : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
      (isClosed_closure (A := A)).isOpen_compl
    -- Moreover, it is contained in `Aᶜ` because `A ⊆ closure A`.
    have h_subset : ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
      intro y hy
      by_contra hAy
      have : y ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure (by
        have : y ∈ A := by
          have : y ∉ Aᶜ := hAy
          simpa using this
        exact this)
      exact hy this
    -- Apply the maximality property of the interior for the open set
    -- `(closure A)ᶜ` contained in `Aᶜ`.
    have h_incl :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
      interior_maximal h_subset h_open
    -- Conclude the desired membership.
    exact h_incl hx

theorem Topology.isClosed_closure_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
  simpa using
    (isClosed_closure :
      IsClosed (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))))
